    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If a founder sets or changes the password of a group, all peers who are offline at the time of this state change will be unable to rejoin the group when they come back online even if they know the password, unless they manually exit the group and join it again with the `tox_group_join` function (e.g. `/close` and then `/join <ID> <password>` in toxic). This causes them to lose their credentials (group identity and group role). \r\n\r\nTo properly address this we need to add an optional password parameter to the `tox_group_reconnect` function. ",
    "closed_at": "2024-12-20T17:18:14Z",
